data.message:
Reservations have been made for our Intergenerational Event at Rev's Bowling! I have 3 important points, so please read on if you are attending or are still interested in coming!

1. PAYMENT: you will pay at the bowling alley - I suggest bringing cash (~$8) to save time as there will be 50+ TNC members attending! 

2. EXTRA SPOTS: we have ~4 spots left. Please comment below if you or a friend would like to take this spot. First come, first serve!

3. PARENTS: children can bowl for free! We can set up a separate 'bumper' lane for children, so please comment below (or message Jenny Lee) if you are bringing your kid(s) and they'd like to be in a kids-only lane so we can reserve that ASAP! 

Have a wonderful rest of the week! :)

REMINDER: Daylight savings time ends tomorrow. We know you can't wait to praise our Lord together, but please enjoy your extra hour of sleep or come join us for pre-service prayer by 11:40am at the TNC office (feel free to ask for directions at the welcoming desk).

***** IMPORTANT ***** 
SUNDAY SERVICE (August 31) WILL NOT BE AT BARNET MARINE PARK.
We will have service at church by 12pm as usual, due to the weather.

There will be a BBQ and activities so stick around after service!

**Please pass on the message to our friends and family who may not frequent Facebook or may not have heard**

Hello Terra Nova!

Carolyn and I just wanted to thank you again for the wonderful installation service last Sunday.

We are so blessed to journey with you in this new season of doing life together.  We are also excited to see what God will bring to fruition in and through this community.

In HIs Grace,

pK

===== ANNOUNCEMENTS =====
1. HOT DOG FUNDRAISER to support Summer Missions:
When – June 22 after each service
Where – Patio area
Price – $5 for Hot Dog or Corn Dog & Drink Combo
We will be selling Home-made Corn Dogs and Premium Hot Dogs with Kimchi and Chili toppings available to raise funds for the mission trips. Volunteers and donations (soda, wieners, supplies etc.) needed. Please contact Helen Park.

2. LADIES’ DODGEBALL
We are looking for members for Church-wide Sports Day on August 2nd. If you are interested in playing, please contact Helen Park.

3. VBS & SUMMER CAMP VOLUNTEERS NEEDED
If you are interested, please signup the volunteer application form by June 15 (today) at the Info Desk. All volunteers must attend the orientation on June 29 (Sun) @4:30pm, Vision Hall.

data.message:
If you haven't heard by now, we made a very difficult announcement last week.  Pastor Tim and I announced our resignation at Terra Nova Church...and believe me, it was not an easy decision for either of us.

As I stood in front of you last week, I had flashbacks rushing through my mind as I looked into many of your eyes.  Though sad, I felt overwhelmed with thankfulness for you.  

This week was tough due to our circumstances.  However, a deeper look really helped me to realize a few important things:

1.  The church is more than a great community of friends, she is the Bride of Christ.  We are loved by Christ and it is His love that keeps us as one body.

2.  Spiritual warfare is real.  Wherever God is at work, the Enemy is at work.  he seeks to hinder, destroy, and distract.  Our circumstance is beyond human activity - it is a combination of God at work and the Enemy trying his best to thwart that work

3.  Practicing reconciliation with one another, reminds us of Jesus reconciling us to God.  The Cross of Christ just became more real to me this week.  When friends look to heal, we see the power of the work of Jesus on the cross.  Reconciliation is the Gospel in action.

4.  Leaders often arise in the midst of crisis.  In my 4 years at TNC, I have not seen greater acts of courageous leadership until the past few weeks...where were you the past 4 year?!  =)   Needless to say, I think (hope and pray) that you will be fine the next 4 and more.

This is just 4...and I will share a lot more in the weeks to come.  But I am encouraged and challenged by each of you.  My last Sunday will be December 22nd.  Pastor Tim's will be sometime in January.  I would love to spend my last few weeks as your Lead Pastor to really bless you and be blessed by you.

===== ANNOUNCEMENTS =====

-  Join us tonight at the "God in My Everything" worship night in Vision Hall at 7:30pm.  Pastor Ken Shigematsu will be sharing some wisdom

-  Daylight Savings is THIS SUNDAY (1 hour back!)

- Townhall meeting will take place at a new location (not the Choe home)...the same room we worship in right after our service.
